Lock the car.
Come in.

122
00:08:20,850 --> 00:08:22,980
You should go back to the driving school.
- Come on! Come on! Come on!

123
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:25,140
Oh wow!

124
00:08:25,220 --> 00:08:26,480
Just what I had in mind!

125
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:28,810
I've been craving for some pizza.

126
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:30,310
Why so generous today?

127
00:08:30,510 --> 00:08:32,020
What's the occasion?

128
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:35,900
Papa, you have a small
pocket and a small heart!

129
00:08:35,980 --> 00:08:37,020
So says the miser.

130
00:08:37,100 --> 00:08:38,890
As if you're super generous.

131
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:41,140
I've been feeding you two
since the past 30 years...

132
00:08:42,520 --> 00:08:45,350
... and what have you spent on this family
from the time you've started earning?

133
00:08:45,770 --> 00:08:47,980
Papa, let me buy my house.

134
00:08:48,140 --> 00:08:52,310
Then my salary will be at
your disposal and you'll be rich!

135
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:55,890
Buying property is no joke!

136
00:08:56,020 --> 00:08:58,440
What do you know about the area?
Whether it has any appreciation?

137
00:08:58,520 --> 00:09:00,310
You have to understand all these
factors. Do you even know any of this?

138
00:09:01,280 --> 00:09:02,850
What makes you think they'll
approve your loan?

139
00:09:03,730 --> 00:09:06,100
Papa, you always underestimate me.

140
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:09,350
To make the impossible possible,
that's what Praful Patel does!

141
00:09:10,010 --> 00:09:11,770
Stop nagging her...

142
00:09:12,020 --> 00:09:13,310
Let her invest.

143
00:09:13,530 --> 00:09:15,850
You're always sitting
behind the counter of a shop.

144
00:09:16,070 --> 00:09:18,850
She's just come home, tired, after
sweeping and mopping floors all day.

145
00:09:18,930 --> 00:09:20,640
Let her eat in peace.
- Mummy, it's not sweeping and mopping.

146
00:09:21,100 --> 00:09:22,230
I work in the hotel industry.

147
00:09:22,310 --> 00:09:23,470
What did I teach you?
- Yeah.

148
00:09:23,550 --> 00:09:24,930
Housekeeping department.
- Yeah, yeah.

149
00:09:25,060 --> 00:09:26,780
Show some respect. - I spend
my day sitting behind a counter.

150
00:09:26,860 --> 00:09:29,230
And you? In front of the computer...

151
00:09:29,420 --> 00:09:31,230
Shopping online all day long.

152
00:09:31,410 --> 00:09:33,640
It's not like I'm buying
gold or diamonds...

153
00:09:33,930 --> 00:09:35,520
I buy groceries for the house.

154
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:37,520
That too because my knees trouble me.

155
00:09:37,890 --> 00:09:39,480
Do you have the money
for a visit to the doctor?

156
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,810
Is it an emergency?

157
00:09:42,190 --> 00:09:43,810
