But if you really want this loan.

526
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:35,290
I suggest you work to improve
your funds over the next few months.

527
00:32:35,460 --> 00:32:37,130
But I have...
- You have a good day.

528
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:39,250
I'll see you later.

529
00:32:40,250 --> 00:32:41,290
Thank you.

530
00:32:59,660 --> 00:33:00,590
Papa!

531
00:33:00,710 --> 00:33:02,500
Why all of a sudden?
Are you feeling alright?

532
00:33:03,290 --> 00:33:05,840
I'm being affectionate.
Can't I?

533
00:33:06,090 --> 00:33:07,040
What's this?

534
00:33:07,290 --> 00:33:09,630
Tomato and pepper curry.

535
00:33:17,130 --> 00:33:21,380
Papa, my friend Salma's father
passed away from a heart attack.

536
00:33:22,070 --> 00:33:26,420
That made me think that I
shouldn't trouble my parents so much.

537
00:33:26,670 --> 00:33:28,210
It happens. It happens.

538
00:33:28,670 --> 00:33:30,460
You shouldn't let it bother
you so much. It happens.

539
00:33:33,220 --> 00:33:36,040
Papa, will you come with
me to see my flat tomorrow?

540
00:33:37,210 --> 00:33:38,250
Why me, all of a sudden?

541
00:33:38,380 --> 00:33:39,790
Not all of a sudden.

542
00:33:39,990 --> 00:33:44,840
I've decided that I won't
do anything without your permission.

543
00:33:45,170 --> 00:33:47,840
Sorry, I was about go buy a house...

544
00:33:47,920 --> 00:33:50,590
... for myself without informing
you or taking your advice.

545
00:33:52,540 --> 00:33:56,210
But papa, I want to invest
in this property only with you.

546
00:33:56,750 --> 00:33:58,340
We will buy a joint property.

547
00:33:59,960 --> 00:34:00,880
Really?

548
00:34:01,500 --> 00:34:02,590
Joint property?

549
00:34:03,630 --> 00:34:06,420
I don't think you know
anything about investment.

550
00:34:07,260 --> 00:34:09,460
If you need help then
why don't you say so.

551
00:34:12,420 --> 00:34:16,090
Okay. Well, why hide
anything from you, papa...

552
00:34:16,380 --> 00:34:18,340
Help me a little?

553
00:34:18,750 --> 00:34:22,750
I can help you,
but I have a condition.

554
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:24,250
Tell me.

555
00:34:24,380 --> 00:34:26,340
We have got a very
good marriage proposal.

556
00:34:26,500 --> 00:34:29,540
He's the son of the owner
of Parekh Hosiery in Rajkot.

557
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:31,040
He's very handsome.

558
00:34:31,540 --> 00:34:32,540
And he is single.

559
00:34:32,840 --> 00:34:35,000
If you meet him...

560
00:34:56,630 --> 00:34:58,710
Welcome back!
- Thank you!

561
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:01,380
So is it a beer or
champagne kinda day?

562
00:35:01,500 --> 00:35:04,540
No drinking.
I have to win my money back.

563
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:06,880
You... you mean you have
to win back the money you lost.

564
00:35:07,120 --> 00:35:08,540
I lost some of my savings.

565
00:35:08,630 --> 00:35:10,000
I am in trouble.

566
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:13,540
Look, I am not supposed to say this...

567
00:35:13,630 --> 00:35:16,540
... but if I were you,
I wouldn't go back and play.

568
00:35:39,590 --> 00:35:40,670
Any more bets?

569
00:35:45,050 --> 00:35:46,130
Okay, no more bets?

570
00:35:47,420 --> 00:35:50,420
Player shows six.
Banker banks on nine.

571
00:35:50,790 --> 00:35:51,790
Banker wins.

572
00:35:57,390 --> 00:35:58,730
Excuse me!

573
00:36:13,790 --> 00:36:15,250
What you want, huh?

574
00:36:15,920 --> 00:36:16,920
Here's a watch.

575
00:36:17,000 --> 00:36:18,880
It's worth 15,000 at least.

576
00:36:20,770 --> 00:36:22,040
What about the car outside?

577
00:36:22,170 --> 00:36:23,920
I'll give you the pink slip, alright?

578
00:36:24,040 --> 00:36:26,590
65,000 any day.

579
00:36:26,960 --> 00:36:31,250
Mike, you owe me 85,000 dollars.

580
00:36:32,220 --> 00:36:34,090
I couldn't get 10 for this.

581
00:36:34,340 --> 00:36:37,040
And your car... is a piece of junk.

582
00:36:37,960 --> 00:36:39,340
Place you bets please.

583
00:36:40,790 --> 00:36:42,090
Ma'am, are you okay?

584
00:36:42,210 --> 00:36:43,840
You guys have taken it all away.

585
00:36:43,920 --> 00:36:46,840
You have stolen everything.
This is cheating!

586
00:36:47,090 --> 00:36:48,290
Ma'am, please calm down.

587
00:36:48,420 --> 00:36:50,040
I want to talk to the owner.

588
00:36:50,130 --> 00:36:51,290
Ma'am, please calm down.

589
00:36:51,420 --> 00:36:54,040
You guys have stolen
my seven years' worth savings.

590
00:36:55,970 --> 00:36:58,210
Calm down or we'll
have to call security.

591
00:37:00,940 --> 00:37:02,130
Call your owner.

592
00:37:02,380 --> 00:37:05,670
I... I will not go anywhere.
I will be here today!

593
00:37:05,810 --> 00:37:07,130
Calm down, calm down.

594
00:37:07,210 --> 00:37:08,290
Are you the owner?

595
00:37:08,420 --> 00:37:10,250
Come on. Come here.

596
00:37:10,380 --> 00:37:12,750
I want to talk to you.
- We can talk. Come here.

597
00:37:12,880 --> 00:37:14,840
Come here. We can talk. We can talk.

598
00:37:20,170 --> 00:37:23,880
Give me my money back. You
are cheaters, all of you are cheaters!

599
00:37:24,040 --> 00:37:25,500
You are all thieves!

600
00:37:25,630 --> 00:37:27,750
I'm not the owner. I'm not the owner.

601
00:37:27,920 --> 00:37:29,380
I'm a private moneylender.

602
00:37:30,630 --> 00:37:32,290
You wanna win all your money back,
don't you?

603
00:37:32,630 --> 00:37:34,250
I lost all my savings.

604
00:37:34,540 --> 00:37:35,840
It's all good, baby.

605
00:37:36,290 --> 00:37:37,670
So how much you need?

606
00:37:38,770 --> 00:37:40,670
You are very sweet.
You want to give me money.

607
00:37:40,790 --> 00:37:41,960
You're a nice man.

608
00:37:42,090 --> 00:37:43,670
It's all good. It's all good.

609
00:37:43,790 --> 00:37:45,130
So how much do you need?

610
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:48,290
25,000?

611
00:37:51,010 --> 00:37:51,960
No.

612
00:37:52,710 --> 00:37:54,460
32,000.
- That's it.

613
00:37:55,210 --> 00:37:57,130
I want to show him a lesson!

614
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:59,250
Hey...
- You cheaters...

615
00:38:00,460 --> 00:38:02,290
I'm going to need your
social security card.

616
00:38:02,500 --> 00:38:04,210
Why?
- Your drivers' license.

617
00:38:05,540 --> 00:38:06,500
Why?

618
00:38:07,670 --> 00:38:10,750
I just gave you 32,000 dollars,
baby girl!

619
00:38:15,290 --> 00:38:18,630
Thank you, buddy.
You're a good person, huh?

620
00:38:18,920 --> 00:38:21,290
Thank you very much.
- Now go show him a lesson.

621
00:38:29,170 --> 00:38:31,030
Place your bets please.

622
00:38:32,960 --> 00:38:33,920
Place your bets please.

623
00:38:34,040 --> 00:38:35,070
Banker.

624
00:38:41,170 --> 00:38:42,170
Banker.

625
00:38:43,500 --> 00:38:45,290
Hi ma'am,
would you like to buy some more?

626
00:38:46,090 --> 00:38:47,420
Place your bets please.

627
00:39:33,390 --> 00:39:34,310
How many 'Ghaatiyas'
(Gujarati snacks)?

628
00:39:34,730 --> 00:39:35,430
Six.

629
00:39:35,520 --> 00:39:36,270
Six.

630
00:39:37,020 --> 00:39:38,020
Four of 'Sev'(Gujarati snacks),
right?

631
00:39:38,360 --> 00:39:39,560
Five.
- 'Sev'.

632
00:39:41,050 --> 00:39:41,980
Five.

633
00:39:42,170 --> 00:39:44,140
'Bhakarwadi'(Gujarati snacks).
One, two, three, four, five, six...

634
00:39:44,230 --> 00:39:45,310
Mohan's new import.

635
00:39:45,480 --> 00:39:47,230
He has imported snacks from Rajkot.
- Four...

636
00:39:47,910 --> 00:39:49,810
Here, taste it.

637
00:39:50,770 --> 00:39:52,100
Chutney...

638
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:54,230
Four...

639
00:39:58,540 --> 00:40:02,210
Papa, you were saying
something the other day...

640
00:40:02,500 --> 00:40:06,920
That if I agree to
meet the boy then...

641
00:40:07,670 --> 00:40:08,920
You were saying something like that.

642
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:10,670
Praful, you...

643
00:40:10,790 --> 00:40:13,000
Now when she is saying
that she'll meet the boy...

644
00:40:13,370 --> 00:40:14,830
... then why are you questioning her?

645
00:40:16,620 --> 00:40:18,290
I suggest you invite
them over tomorrow itself.

646
00:40:19,670 --> 00:40:20,500
Done.

647
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:21,670
We'll call them over.

648
00:40:25,580 --> 00:40:29,420
Praful, that's Mr. and Mrs. Parekh.

649
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,080
You remember Kaushal?

650
00:40:31,500 --> 00:40:34,370
He has a hosiery shop in Rajkot.
He is his cousin.

651
00:40:34,790 --> 00:40:35,790
How are you, auntie?

652
00:40:35,960 --> 00:40:37,120
How are you, uncle?

653
00:40:37,460 --> 00:40:38,500
All good, dear.

654
00:40:38,620 --> 00:40:40,620
He's Kaushal's elder son.

655
00:40:40,750 --> 00:40:41,500
Sameer.
- Hello.

656
00:40:41,580 --> 00:40:42,270
Hello.

657
00:40:44,200 --> 00:40:45,540
You work in a hotel?

658
00:40:45,990 --> 00:40:47,250
Housekeeping department.

659
00:40:47,370 --> 00:40:48,210
Very good.

660
00:40:48,350 --> 00:40:50,120
She will keep the house clean.

661
00:40:50,760 --> 00:40:54,290
Anyway, a housewife
is a housekeeper, right?

662
00:40:55,170 --> 00:40:57,460
Dear, you have been working
in the same hotel for seven years?

663
00:40:57,540 --> 00:40:58,170
Yes.

664
00:40:58,290 --> 00:41:00,670
After the divorce, right?

665
00:41:02,750 --> 00:41:05,960
Sameer, you have come here for MBA?

666
00:41:06,080 --> 00:41:06,960
Yes, auntie.

667
00:41:07,370 --> 00:41:10,750
Your aunt told me that
you have a new startup plan.

668
00:41:10,870 --> 00:41:14,290
Yes, actually I plan
to make a mobile app.

669
00:41:14,420 --> 00:41:15,330
Wonderful.

670
00:41:15,710 --> 00:41:17,670
Nowadays everyone uses apps.

671
00:41:17,790 --> 00:41:22,120
My wife is an online champion.
She does everything online.

672
00:41:22,460 --> 00:41:26,040
Prayers happening in Atlanta
but pundit sitting in Nathdwara.

673
00:41:28,540 --> 00:41:30,830
Actually,
my app too is related to our culture.

674
00:41:30,920 --> 00:41:33,830
You can view all religious
places in India through that.

675
00:41:34,120 --> 00:41:35,790
You can watch its live telecast.

676
00:41:36,040 --> 00:41:38,120
Press a button and offer flowers.

677
00:41:38,400 --> 00:41:40,500
Press another button
and feed the poor.

678
00:41:40,620 --> 00:41:41,670
Instant karma.

679
00:41:41,790 --> 00:41:43,170
Hail Lord Shiva.

680
00:41:43,290 --> 00:41:44,290
Wonderful.

681
00:41:47,500 --> 00:41:51,120
I think the kids should
talk to each other.

682
00:41:53,600 --> 00:41:55,370
Yes, sure.

683
00:42:17,920 --> 00:42:19,210
Why do you want to get married?

684
00:42:19,450 --> 00:42:20,580
For a green card?

685
00:42:21,420 --> 00:42:22,330
No.

686
00:42:23,750 --> 00:42:25,250
I mean I am doing my MBA here.

687
00:42:25,370 --> 00:42:27,790
I can easily spend two years
here without getting married.

688
00:42:29,620 --> 00:42:31,710
I want to get married
because I am alone.

689
00:42:32,750 --> 00:42:36,080
Life will get better
if I find a life partner.

690
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:41,690
Anyway, if two people earn
then the expenses get divided.

691
00:42:41,770 --> 00:42:44,580
So your wife will earn
and you will educate yourself?

692
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,170
No.

693
00:42:46,620 --> 00:42:48,040
I have worked for two years.

694
00:42:48,500 --> 00:42:49,920
I have money for my education.

695
00:42:52,770 --> 00:42:54,920
I wanted to be a self-made man.

696
00:42:56,130 --> 00:42:57,620
And I have a plan for that too.

697
00:42:58,220 --> 00:42:59,460
I just need a purpose.

698
00:43:00,170 --> 00:43:01,210
I am searching for it.

699
00:43:03,320 --> 00:43:07,040
You think you will get purpose,
love, companionship...

700
00:43:07,120 --> 00:43:10,870
... all nicely wrapped
in a package called marriage?

701
00:43:11,730 --> 00:43:12,710
I don't know.

702
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:16,330
I will try to be true to
this relationship to the best I can.

703
00:43:17,460 --> 00:43:19,000
Then we will see where life takes us.

704
00:43:19,380 --> 00:43:22,540
I too gave my best to a relationship.

705
00:43:22,890 --> 00:43:24,460
Look at what happened to me.

706
00:43:24,830 --> 00:43:27,370
What if life brings
you to a similar juncture?

707
00:43:27,500 --> 00:43:30,250
What if you are standing
where I am standing today?

708
00:43:30,920 --> 00:43:32,040
So what's wrong?

709
00:43:32,750 --> 00:43:34,250
The weather is wonderful.

710
00:43:34,750 --> 00:43:35,920
It's not raining either.

711
00:43:37,930 --> 00:43:40,120
And I don't think
my company is that bad either.

712
00:43:40,620 --> 00:43:41,580
Right?

713
00:43:45,390 --> 00:43:47,500
You tend to romanticize things.

714
00:43:47,680 --> 00:43:49,670
You too are quite frank.

715
00:43:51,140 --> 00:43:52,310
It was a pleasure to meet you.

716
00:43:57,000 --> 00:43:58,080
Shall we go back?

717
00:43:58,830 --> 00:43:59,620
Let's go...

718
00:44:04,790 --> 00:44:05,920
Praful.

719
00:44:07,540 --> 00:44:08,330
She's asleep.

720
00:44:08,420 --> 00:44:09,580
No.

721
00:44:13,460 --> 00:44:16,170
Praful, I liked this boy.

722
00:44:18,300 --> 00:44:22,870
Mummy, papa told me that
he would help me if I meet the boy.

723
00:44:23,360 --> 00:44:24,330
What do you mean?

724
00:44:24,930 --> 00:44:28,920
He told me that he would
help me if I meet the boy.

725
00:44:29,810 --> 00:44:31,920
Really? When did that happen?

726
00:44:32,550 --> 00:44:33,290
Mummy...

727
00:44:34,000 --> 00:44:36,580
Tell me, how did you like Sameer?

728
00:44:37,930 --> 00:44:41,200
I'll never get such a house
again in minority housing.

729
00:44:44,430 --> 00:44:45,420
Okay, dear.

730
00:44:45,670 --> 00:44:46,870
Don't worry.

731
00:44:47,610 --> 00:44:51,710
I'll talk to your father
when he's in a good mood.

732
00:44:53,670 --> 00:44:56,420
But at least tell me
what you though of Sameer...

733
00:44:57,340 --> 00:44:58,250
Good night.

734
00:44:59,170 --> 00:45:00,120
Good night.

735
00:45:09,540 --> 00:45:11,000
Hello, Mr. Steven.

736
00:45:11,580 --> 00:45:12,620
Yes, Ms. Patel.

737
00:45:15,430 --> 00:45:16,960
I need some more time.

738
00:45:17,160 --> 00:45:20,080
I'm... I'm sorry Ms. Patel,
but that house is sold.

739
00:45:22,750 --> 00:45:24,120
That house is sold?

740
00:45:24,580 --> 00:45:25,790
Yes.

741
00:45:27,040 --> 00:45:28,420
But you said you will wait for me.

742
00:45:28,500 --> 00:45:31,250
I know, but it has been a while
since you called back, Ms. Patel.

743
00:45:31,710 --> 00:45:33,920
I am sorry I just
couldn't wait anymore.

744
00:45:57,130 --> 00:45:57,870
Granny!

745
00:45:58,080 --> 00:46:01,080
Oh my baby! Come here. Come here.

746
00:46:02,510 --> 00:46:03,290
How are you?

747
00:46:03,430 --> 00:46:04,920
I am fine.

748
00:46:05,170 --> 00:46:10,290
But you neither call,
whatsapp or snapchat.

749
00:46:10,420 --> 00:46:13,920
Don't you miss Nathdwara?
- I do.

750
00:46:14,330 --> 00:46:16,120
Then why this half smile?

751
00:46:16,280 --> 00:46:17,750
It's a full smile.

752
00:46:18,670 --> 00:46:20,710
But it doesn't reach your eyes.

753
00:46:24,500 --> 00:46:27,540
I had found a nice
house in minority housing.

754
00:46:27,720 --> 00:46:29,620
But I lost that deal.

755
00:46:29,830 --> 00:46:31,870
It's okay, you'll find another one.

756
00:46:34,040 --> 00:46:36,460
Oh, my God. Him?
What is he doing here?

757
00:46:36,580 --> 00:46:37,250
Who?

758
00:46:37,370 --> 00:46:41,080
The boy who had come to see me.
- Which one?

759
00:46:41,170 --> 00:46:45,040
That one. The stupid looking one...
oh shit, he saw me.

760
00:46:46,420 --> 00:46:48,290
Hi, Praful.
- Hello.

761
00:46:49,000 --> 00:46:50,080
My granny.

762
00:46:50,170 --> 00:46:52,500
I seek your blessings.
- It's okay. God bless you.

763
00:46:53,460 --> 00:46:56,170
Why do I feel as if
she was badmouthing me?

764
00:46:56,500 --> 00:46:58,000
It's not that...

765
00:46:58,140 --> 00:47:01,750
She was saying that sweet
boy had come to see her.

766
00:47:02,170 --> 00:47:03,620
Did she say that?
- Yes.

767
00:47:05,370 --> 00:47:06,870
Does she like this sweet boy?

768
00:47:08,770 --> 00:47:09,830
She likes you.

769
00:47:10,260 --> 00:47:12,120
It's not so.

770
00:47:14,100 --> 00:47:15,960
I still haven't thought about that.

771
00:47:16,100 --> 00:47:17,540
After all she's a girl.

772
00:47:19,080 --> 00:47:20,330
This...

773
00:47:20,670 --> 00:47:23,500
I knew I'd find Praful
here so I brought this along.

774
00:47:23,920 --> 00:47:24,960
What's this?

775
00:47:25,210 --> 00:47:26,370
Have a look.

776
00:47:31,540 --> 00:47:32,840
This belongs to my grandma.

777
00:47:32,960 --> 00:47:36,000
I wanted to give it to
the one I'd spend my life with.

778
00:47:36,440 --> 00:47:39,660
You still carry your grandma's
last memento in your pocket?

779
00:47:40,500 --> 00:47:41,620
It's not so.

780
00:47:41,890 --> 00:47:44,750
You tend to have your heart broken a
few times by the time you reach this age.

781
00:47:45,210 --> 00:47:46,420
This is its third copy.

782
00:47:48,790 --> 00:47:53,370
Third copy or the fourth copy,
it should be its last copy.

783
00:47:53,500 --> 00:47:54,670
You are absolutely right.

784
00:47:55,250 --> 00:47:56,000
Keep it, dear.

785
00:47:56,080 --> 00:47:57,290
Granny!
- Take it.

786
00:47:57,370 --> 00:47:59,170
Let's go.
The function is about to begin.

787
00:48:00,120 --> 00:48:01,170
